OL,6,FHe explains: "Whilst they've got a
OL,7,Fduty to maintain, it doesn't include a
OL,8,Fprivate right of action for
OL,9,Findividuals who have suffered loss,
OL,10,Finjury or damage as a result of a
OL,11,Fdefect in the highway.
OL,13,F"UK legislation includes an express
OL,14,Fpermission for a private right of
OL,15,Faction, so people there who suffer
OL,16,Fslips and trips are entitled to bring
OL,17,Fa claim and the court will assess it
OL,18,Fin the usual way.
